  "response": "Here are a few memorable dialogues from the movie Masaan that capture the essence of the film:\n\n1. \"Yeh sheher bahut bada hai... bahut saare log hain. Har ek ki apni kahani hai.\" \n(This city is very big... there are many people. Each one has their own story.)\n\n2. \"Kabhi kabhi lagta hai apun hi bahut akela hai is duniya mein.\"\n(Sometimes it feels like I'm very alone in this world.)\n\n3. \"Zindagi mein kuch toh log kahenge, logon ka kaam hai kehna.\"\n(People will always have something to say in life, it's their job to talk.)\n\nThese dialogues reflect the movie's themes of love, loss, societal pressures, and individual struggles. The film, directed by Neeraj Ghaywan, is known for its nuanced storytelling and powerful dialogue that captures the complexity of human emotions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these dialogues or discuss the film's context?",
